{
  "stem": "4967.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Lithuanian took the motorbike, and they let my father free.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we remained for another two weeks at this military men, where we stayed for this period, which was an unrest.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a pogrom, especially in [INAUDIBLE], They killed the Jewish people, murdered them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when the Germans came in, the Lithuanians will not allow it, to kill the Jewish people or do anything to them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was big posters in town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First of all, you shouldn't-- anybody who [NON-ENGLISH], means robs or rapes, or do anything to anybody will be bitterly punished.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a few months later came out the law that the Jewish people must surrender their valuable, gold, silver, diamonds, and radio receivers or transmitters.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all the musical instruments must be surrendered to the Germans in certain places.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whatever we had, we had to give-- to give it in to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you didn't get a receipt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think some people even got a receipt that they surrendered their valuables.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then came out an order that a certain date-- I don't know, I think it was in September-- that all Jewish people from Kovno must move from the main city to [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1942.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, '41 or 42.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think the ghetto established in '42.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not-- I think-- I think so.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you should have seen how the Jewish people are [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Horses with waggons and cart their belongings and schlepping furniture and schlepping whatever they possessed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the ghetto was established in a matter of 15 or 20 days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We actually settled in a house which belonged to my great uncle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was not far from a main road who connects Kovno to another city.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
